    "The colored points represent the image model visibilities from each method, with station gains derived from each method's internal self-calibration procedure applied to the image model visibilities.",
    "Below each visibility amplitude figure are the normalized residuals for each image, which is the difference between the gray and the colored points, divided by the uncertainty of the gray data points.",
    "The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024) The difference of the flux densities between F tot and F cpct implies there is some emission outside the compact region.",
    "However, its structure (e.g., scale and direction) is unconstrained by the data (Sect. 4).",
    "The sub-milliarcsecond scale jet is not detected by the 2017 and 2018 EHT data, but is clearly seen in the 3 mm images (Hada et al. 2016; Kim et al. 2018a; Lu et al. 2023)."
